              Indexed by search engines. Readable on every device. Works in 
              WhatsApp, email, web pages, and government portals — no font needed.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
          Despite this, KrutiDev remains in active use across India — millions 
          of documents, exam papers, court records, and newspaper archives exist 
          only in legacy font format. Our free KrutiDev to Unicode converter 
          handles the full character set including complex conjuncts (स्त्र, 
          क्ष, ज्ञ), reph placement (र्), and Devanagari numerals — the tricky 
          edge cases that simpler tools get wrong.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- SECTION 4 — WHO USES THIS TOOL? -->
      <section class="border-t border-slate-200/60 dark:border-slate-800/60 pt-10">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-extrabold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100 tracking-tight">
          Who uses this tool?
        </h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 dark:text-slate-500 mt-1 mb-6 font-medium">
          Real people with real daily workflows — not just hobbyists.
        </p>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          <!-- Card 1 -->
          <div class="border-l-2 border-brand-600 dark:border-brand-500 bg-slate-100/50 dark:bg-slate-900/40 p-4 rounded-r-lg">
            <h3 class="font-extrabold text-sm text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100 mb-1">
